From the way you&#39;ve phrased your question it seems that you think that security rules would automatically filter the data. That is not true: security rules only ensures that the user has permission to read the data they&#39;re trying to read. This happens when you attach the listener, and is not in any way based on the actual data in your database.

For more on this, see the section [rules are not filters](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/security/securing-data#rules_are_not_filters) in the documentation, some of the many previous [questions on the topic](https://stackoverflow.com/search?q=%5Bfirebase%5D+rules+are+not+filters), and the documentation on [securely querying](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/security/securing-data#query-based_rules).

